1
00:00:13,120 --> 00:00:20,890
♫ Let's hold hands tightly and match our footsteps  ♫

2
00:00:27,881 --> 00:00:30,301
[Adapted from Joo Young Hyun's webtoon, "I Don't Want to Do Anything"]

3
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:40,061
[Summer Strike]

4
00:00:40,061 --> 00:00:46,136
[All characters, regions, groups, and organizations are fictional. Animal scenes complied to animal welfare guidelines.]

5
00:00:56,281 --> 00:00:58,831
Hey! Drive a bit slower!

6
00:00:58,831 --> 00:01:00,521
I'm sorry. Are you okay?

7
00:01:00,521 --> 00:01:02,871
If you want to go bathroom, just stop for a second!

8
00:01:02,871 --> 00:01:04,171
No, I'm fine.

9
00:01:04,171 --> 00:01:07,351
I'm not okay. I'm scared.

10
00:01:09,471 --> 00:01:12,311
We're here.

11
00:01:13,161 --> 00:01:16,331
I won't let it go if I get a ticket.

12
00:01:18,481 --> 00:01:20,861
I'll be right back after getting the files. Why don't you use the bathroom?

13
00:01:20,861 --> 00:01:22,741
No, I'm okay.

14
00:01:22,741 --> 00:01:24,351
Why? I'll drive you home.

15
00:01:24,351 --> 00:01:26,730
- I'll get going first.
- Where are you going?

16
00:01:26,730 --> 00:01:28,381
Get home safe!

17
00:01:28,381 --> 00:01:29,540
Hey, my car key!

18
00:01:29,540 --> 00:01:31,530
It's in the car!

19
00:01:32,271 --> 00:01:34,141
What's up with him?

20
00:01:57,621 --> 00:01:59,711
[Seon Ah]

21
00:02:12,131 --> 00:02:15,541
[Seon Ah]

22
00:02:18,588 --> 00:02:20,031
What is it?

23
00:02:20,031 --> 00:02:22,659
Do you want to go for a walk?

24
00:02:22,659 --> 00:02:25,679
Can we just skip today?

25
00:02:26,772 --> 00:02:30,182
Okay. Let's go out for a walk.

26
00:02:32,111 --> 00:02:33,671
Let's go.

27
00:02:41,881 --> 00:02:43,771
Mr. Librarian?

28
00:02:59,701 --> 00:03:03,161
What brings you here at this hour?

29
00:03:03,161 --> 00:03:04,741
I came too late, right?

30
00:03:04,741 --> 00:03:06,421
Not at all.

31
00:03:12,171 --> 00:03:15,851
Well, everyone already left.

32
00:03:18,771 --> 00:03:24,168
I was just about to take a walk with Gyeo Wool.

33
00:03:24,168 --> 00:03:28,221
If it's in the same direction, can I walk with you?

34
00:03:28,221 --> 00:03:30,121
Shall we?

35
00:03:33,091 --> 00:03:37,871
But why are you sweating so much?

36
00:03:38,941 --> 00:03:42,801
It's a bit hot today.

37
00:03:44,241 --> 00:03:46,181
Is it?

38
00:03:47,381 --> 00:03:51,761
Do you really jog every day at that hour?

39
00:03:51,761 --> 00:03:54,571
You live such a disciplined life.

40
00:03:54,571 --> 00:03:57,911
I naturally wake at that hour.

41
00:03:57,911 --> 00:04:00,041
I don't usually sleep well.

42
00:04:00,041 --> 00:04:02,891
In times like that, just don't open your eyes.

43
00:04:02,891 --> 00:04:05,921
If you keep your eyes closed, you'll fall back asleep.

44
00:04:05,921 --> 00:04:09,311
I once slept 14 hours doing so.

45
00:04:09,311 --> 00:04:11,271
- "Fourteen hours"?
- Yes.

46
00:04:11,271 --> 00:04:16,520
Of course, I had a regular life back in Seoul.

47
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:19,881
No, I'm envious (of sleeping well).

48
00:04:26,321 --> 00:04:29,191
I'll go this way now.

49
00:04:29,191 --> 00:04:31,601
Get home safely.

50
00:04:31,601 --> 00:04:34,230
- See you later.
- Okay.

51
00:04:34,741 --> 00:04:37,141
Bye, Gyeo Wool.

52
00:04:40,041 --> 00:04:42,191
Wait, Mr. Librarian!

53
00:04:50,751 --> 00:04:52,791
It's nothing.

54
00:04:52,791 --> 00:04:54,651
Good night.

55
00:04:54,651 --> 00:04:57,560
- All right. Get home safely.
- Okay.

56
00:05:00,691 --> 00:05:02,411
Let's go home.

57
00:05:05,430 --> 00:05:08,116
I couldn't wake early if I wanted to, right?

58
00:05:08,116 --> 00:05:10,516
Right, Gyeo Wool?

59
00:05:15,431 --> 00:05:16,651
Hello.

60
00:05:16,651 --> 00:05:19,251
Oh, Yeo Reum.

61
00:05:19,251 --> 00:05:21,801
I'll try working out from now on as well.

62
00:05:21,801 --> 00:05:23,611
Really?

63
00:05:24,761 --> 00:05:26,971
It's better if you run slower.

64
00:05:26,971 --> 00:05:28,971
Otherwise, you'll tire faster.

65
00:05:31,271 --> 00:05:35,031
But how is it you don't even breathe audibly?
[Summer Strike: Episode 7]

66
00:05:51,381 --> 00:05:55,021
No, I must catch up on sleep.

67
00:05:55,021 --> 00:05:57,771
Let's go to sleep.

68
00:05:59,301 --> 00:06:02,391
I can go to sleep now.

69
00:06:03,591 --> 00:06:07,981
I can't do this. I think some soju is left somewhere.

70
00:06:11,747 --> 00:06:13,381
Yeo Reum.

71
00:06:13,381 --> 00:06:15,491
Oh, good morning.

72
00:06:15,491 --> 00:06:17,251
You really made it.

73
00:06:17,251 --> 00:06:19,581
Early morning jogging was great last time.

74
00:06:19,581 --> 00:06:22,571
Then shall we

75
00:06:22,571 --> 00:06:26,071
meet in front of the library daily and go jogging?

76
00:06:26,071 --> 00:06:26,901
Every morning?

77
00:06:26,901 --> 00:06:31,081
I've planned a variety of running courses as well.

78
00:06:34,253 --> 00:06:39,781
But it's very early morning so short courses are best, right?

79
00:06:39,781 --> 00:06:41,931
Of course.

80
00:06:43,071 --> 00:06:46,615
But really, you don't have to worry about me.

81
00:06:46,615 --> 00:06:50,001
Please run as you normally do, Mr. Librarian.

82
00:06:50,001 --> 00:06:52,721
I'm Dae Beom.

83
00:06:52,721 --> 00:06:54,161
Pardon?

84
00:06:54,161 --> 00:06:58,341
My name is Dae Beom, Yeo Reum.

85
00:07:03,031 --> 00:07:04,631
Okay.

86
00:07:13,271 --> 00:07:15,691
Wow, it's really hard!

87
00:07:21,401 --> 00:07:24,371
I think he will like this.

88
00:07:25,291 --> 00:07:27,611
Yeo Reum!

89
00:07:28,381 --> 00:07:31,671
Yeo Reum, are you home?

90
00:07:31,671 --> 00:07:33,041
Grandma!

91
00:07:33,041 --> 00:07:35,471
Aigoo! You were up there!

92
00:07:35,471 --> 00:07:37,751
How are you?

93
00:07:38,881 --> 00:07:42,131
Grandma, what brings you here?

94
00:07:42,131 --> 00:07:43,371
Why don't you come inside?

95
00:07:43,371 --> 00:07:45,921
No, I must go soon.

96
00:07:46,811 --> 00:07:53,401
I have... a favor to ask you, Yeo Reum.

97
00:07:53,401 --> 00:07:57,081
What is it? Please feel free to ask.

98
00:07:57,081 --> 00:08:01,811
A person I know has a house in Dongcheon Valley.

99
00:08:01,811 --> 00:08:07,611
By any chance... could you go on a trip there with my Bom?

100
00:08:07,611 --> 00:08:09,841
Me?

101
00:08:09,841 --> 00:08:12,411
My poor baby had a tough time.

102
00:08:12,411 --> 00:08:16,920
But I didn't do anything for her as her grandmother.

103
00:08:17,521 --> 00:08:20,591
You're not asking a favor; you're giving me a gift.

104
00:08:20,591 --> 00:08:22,781
Thank you for saying that.

105
00:08:22,781 --> 00:08:25,861
Thanks to you, I'll also get a summer trip.

106
00:08:25,861 --> 00:08:28,091
Thank you.

107
00:08:28,821 --> 00:08:30,581
- Dae Beom.
- Yes?

108
00:08:30,581 --> 00:08:33,301
Dae Beom, Dae Beom, hurry here.

109
00:08:36,651 --> 00:08:38,360
Look at this.

110
00:08:38,811 --> 00:08:41,001
[A New Interpretation of Quantum Mechanics Surprised the Physics World]

111
00:08:41,001 --> 00:08:44,411
Your professor is amazing. He's incredible!

112
00:08:45,341 --> 00:08:47,101
- Wait, come here.
- Yes?

113
00:08:47,101 --> 00:08:48,950
Come here. What's this?

114
00:08:48,950 --> 00:08:51,840
Wait, what is it? What?

115
00:08:51,840 --> 00:08:55,041
- What is it?
- You... you have sand there.

116
00:08:57,091 --> 00:09:00,981
Have I poop on my hand? Why make a fuss?

117
00:09:00,981 --> 00:09:02,581
I'm sorry.

118
00:09:34,370 --> 00:09:37,860
[One minute is enough time to sterilize books and keep them healthy!]

119
00:09:47,401 --> 00:09:49,241
You're here.

120
00:09:50,301 --> 00:09:52,561
How are you?

121
00:10:08,421 --> 00:10:12,361
[Angok Public Library]

122
00:10:12,361 --> 00:10:14,431
Yeo Reum!

123
00:10:18,161 --> 00:10:20,531
Are you going home already?

124
00:10:20,531 --> 00:10:22,211
Yes.

125
00:10:24,171 --> 00:10:26,651
Well, wait...

126
00:10:26,651 --> 00:10:31,061
You'll eat dinner tonight, right? Are you busy tonight?

127
00:10:31,061 --> 00:10:34,351
Why? Shall we go to a movie?

128
00:10:34,351 --> 00:10:36,461
- "A movie"?
- Sorry?

129
00:10:39,631 --> 00:10:41,491
No, I don't mean that.

130
00:10:41,491 --> 00:10:45,541
There's a movie that I wanted to watch,

131
00:10:45,541 --> 00:10:47,941
and it just came to theaters.

132
00:10:52,241 --> 00:10:54,971
- Will you go with me?
- Shall we watch it together?

133
00:10:56,761 --> 00:11:00,421
If it's okay with you, shall we watch it together?

134
00:11:00,421 --> 00:11:02,421
Shall we?

135
00:11:04,831 --> 00:11:06,931
- This looks heavy. Let me help you.
- No, it's okay.

136
00:11:06,931 --> 00:11:10,051
- No, I'll help.
- No, it's heavy for you.

137
00:11:10,051 --> 00:11:11,681
I'm sorry!

138
00:11:11,681 --> 00:11:14,301
It's not your fault. It's heavy.

139
00:11:16,161 --> 00:11:20,571
Also, I already got the movie tickets for both of us.

140
00:11:20,571 --> 00:11:23,391
"Already"? Wait, that's heavy.

141
00:11:24,571 --> 00:11:26,481
Can you help carry only one?

142
00:11:45,151 --> 00:11:46,271
Bom, what will you do for summer vacation?

143
00:11:46,271 --> 00:11:48,371
I don't know. It's none of your business.

144
00:11:48,371 --> 00:11:49,891
- Noona!
- Unnie!

145
00:11:49,891 --> 00:11:51,421
Hi.

146
00:11:51,421 --> 00:11:52,541
Did you guys skip school?

147
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:55,701
What? No, it's the last day of the semester.

148
00:11:55,701 --> 00:11:57,931
- Already?
- Yes.

149
00:11:57,931 --> 00:12:00,011
I don't notice as I'm always all vacation.

150
00:12:00,011 --> 00:12:02,211
But it's too bad.

151
00:12:02,211 --> 00:12:06,371
I was about to go to school diligently from now on.

152
00:12:06,371 --> 00:12:09,011
But why do you smile when you say that?

153
00:12:09,011 --> 00:12:11,551
Mind your own business.

154
00:12:11,551 --> 00:12:16,221
By the way, my grandma was packing stuff for you this morning.

155
00:12:16,221 --> 00:12:19,191
Yes, I received it.

156
00:12:19,191 --> 00:12:21,771
Did she say anything else besides that?

157
00:12:21,771 --> 00:12:25,811
She told me to go on a trip with you.

158
00:12:25,811 --> 00:12:27,931
Really? "A trip"?

159
00:12:27,931 --> 00:12:30,761
Great! I also wanted to go on a trip.

160
00:12:30,761 --> 00:12:33,401
Where will we go? To a beach? Or a mountain?

161
00:12:33,401 --> 00:12:37,651
Your grandmother said she knows someone with a house in Dongcheon.

162
00:12:37,651 --> 00:12:40,421
"Dongcheon"? Where is that?

163
00:12:40,421 --> 00:12:43,111
That's not important. What should I prepare first?

164
00:12:43,111 --> 00:12:45,991
Why do you think you are definitely coming with us?

165
00:12:45,991 --> 00:12:49,221
That's right. Let's ask Hyung Dae Beom to come with us.

166
00:12:49,221 --> 00:12:51,581
I'll get his "yes."

167
00:12:51,581 --> 00:12:53,581
Hyung! Hyung Dae Beom.

168
00:12:54,931 --> 00:12:57,021
You guys treat the library like your home.

169
00:12:57,021 --> 00:12:58,511
I'm sorry.

170
00:12:58,511 --> 00:13:00,401
The thing is...

171
00:13:08,031 --> 00:13:11,131
Look! The river in Dongcheon is crazy!

172
00:13:11,131 --> 00:13:14,791
I don't need to see it. Why look it up when we'll see it in person soon?

173
00:13:14,791 --> 00:13:16,341
I said it was fine.

174
00:13:16,341 --> 00:13:18,251
Wait, I...

175
00:13:18,251 --> 00:13:22,421
I have plans today.

176
00:13:22,421 --> 00:13:24,131
Why don't you leave first?

177
00:13:24,131 --> 00:13:27,291
"Plans"? Whom do you have plans with?

178
00:13:27,291 --> 00:13:29,901
I get it, Unnie. We'll go first.

179
00:13:30,511 --> 00:13:33,061
- Get home safely!
- Fighting!

180
00:13:33,061 --> 00:13:34,250
What groceries do we get for the trip?

181
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:36,400
Let's get meat first.

182
00:13:42,501 --> 00:13:44,261
Let's get dinner.

183
00:13:44,261 --> 00:13:48,731
Noona, I'm sorry. I have plans tonight.

184
00:13:49,411 --> 00:13:51,171
With Yeo Reum?

185
00:13:51,171 --> 00:13:52,861
Yes.

186
00:14:02,061 --> 00:14:04,530
- Ahn Dae Beom.
- Yes?

187
00:14:04,530 --> 00:14:08,421
I'm not just a Noona to you, right?

188
00:14:09,271 --> 00:14:10,831
Right.

189
00:14:17,651 --> 00:14:19,601
Noona, that hurts.

190
00:14:23,061 --> 00:14:27,031
I feel like I'm getting hurt by you as well.

191
00:14:38,271 --> 00:14:40,171
[Angok Public Library]

192
00:14:52,861 --> 00:14:54,921
Oh, Yeo Reum!

193
00:14:56,761 --> 00:14:58,751
I'll just lock the door quickly.

194
00:14:58,751 --> 00:15:00,821
Take your time.

195
00:15:07,871 --> 00:15:10,401
- Sh-Shall we go?
- Yes.

196
00:15:10,401 --> 00:15:12,361
Did you wait a long time?

197
00:15:12,361 --> 00:15:15,961
No, I also came out just now.

198
00:15:18,091 --> 00:15:19,981
What am I doing?

199
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:38,871
This area has many trees.

200
00:15:44,141 --> 00:15:48,581
How can you not check if you turned off the headlight?

201
00:15:48,581 --> 00:15:51,221
How can you be so distracted?

202
00:15:58,071 --> 00:16:01,161
Don't turn off the engine right away.

203
00:16:01,161 --> 00:16:05,721
Be thankful to me! Who would come and jump start your car in the middle of the night?

204
00:16:05,721 --> 00:16:08,020
And you call the tow truck. Why call me?

205
00:16:08,020 --> 00:16:10,210
You're so strange.

206
00:16:12,201 --> 00:16:14,401
Why are you acting solemn?

207
00:16:17,731 --> 00:16:20,081
Jo Ji Young, are you crying?

208
00:16:27,021 --> 00:16:30,091
Did something happen to you?

209
00:16:30,091 --> 00:16:34,011
I don't know. I feel pathetic.

210
00:16:35,021 --> 00:16:36,711
All right. I get it, Ji Young.

211
00:16:36,711 --> 00:16:40,471
Just cry. You'll feel better if you let it all out.

212
00:16:42,431 --> 00:16:45,591
It's really annoying.

213
00:16:53,911 --> 00:16:56,441
I'm fine now. Can you get a tissue?

214
00:16:56,441 --> 00:16:59,111
"A tissue"? Is it in your car?

215
00:17:01,441 --> 00:17:04,281
- Under there!
- Yes, I found it.

216
00:17:13,031 --> 00:17:15,491
Enjoy your movie.

217
00:17:16,341 --> 00:17:18,071
Here.

218
00:17:18,951 --> 00:17:21,291
You can't enter with these tickets.

219
00:17:21,291 --> 00:17:24,961
- Why not?
- You got tickets for next week, not tonight.

220
00:17:24,961 --> 00:17:26,831
This movie is released next week.

221
00:17:26,831 --> 00:17:28,531
That can't be.

222
00:17:28,531 --> 00:17:31,751
If you look at the date right there...

223
00:17:31,751 --> 00:17:33,811
You're right.

224
00:17:37,101 --> 00:17:40,641
How did I miss this?

225
00:17:41,301 --> 00:17:42,570
I'm sorry.

226
00:17:42,570 --> 00:17:44,600
No, it's okay!

227
00:17:48,741 --> 00:17:53,251
Well, then do you want to go for fried chicken and beer?

228
00:17:53,251 --> 00:17:55,671
"Fried chicken and beer"?

229
00:17:55,671 --> 00:18:01,641
Actually, earlier, I was going to ask you out for fried chicken and beer.

230
00:18:02,971 --> 00:18:04,230
I would love to.

231
00:18:04,230 --> 00:18:05,610
Really?

232
00:18:05,611 --> 00:18:08,171
I'll look for a place now.

233
00:18:09,931 --> 00:18:12,511
If we go that way,

234
00:18:12,511 --> 00:18:15,461
it's an old place with delicious fried chicken.

235
00:18:15,461 --> 00:18:17,971
And going in that direction

236
00:18:17,971 --> 00:18:22,971
is a spacious, clean one, but reviews say their chicken is just okay.

237
00:18:22,971 --> 00:18:26,631
Then this way, a place has outdoor tables.

238
00:18:26,631 --> 00:18:29,871
And the review said their beer is really great.

239
00:18:29,871 --> 00:18:32,741
I guess you looked it up already.

240
00:18:32,741 --> 00:18:35,861
Yes, just in case.

241
00:18:36,601 --> 00:18:38,411
I'll choose...

242
00:18:39,061 --> 00:18:40,731
the third place.

243
00:18:40,731 --> 00:18:43,961
Delicious beer is harder to find than chicken.

244
00:18:45,211 --> 00:18:46,861
How long to get there?

245
00:18:46,861 --> 00:18:48,731
It takes about 10 minutes.

246
00:18:48,731 --> 00:18:50,821
It's quite close.

247
00:18:53,521 --> 00:18:55,551
Why are you suddenly running?

248
00:18:55,551 --> 00:18:57,941
It's a 10-minute run.

249
00:19:00,301 --> 00:19:01,600
Do you want to walk instead?

250
00:19:01,600 --> 00:19:03,740
No, let's run!

251
00:19:03,741 --> 00:19:05,431
It's 30 minutes to walk.

252
00:19:05,431 --> 00:19:08,081
Then let's get there in five minutes!

253
00:19:14,850 --> 00:19:16,930
It's so good.

254
00:19:16,930 --> 00:19:19,780
This place has great beer.

255
00:19:20,670 --> 00:19:24,291
Who first thought of eating fried chicken and beer together?

256
00:19:25,490 --> 00:19:31,011
The one who invented this first needs an award!

257
00:19:31,930 --> 00:19:33,801
Please use this.

258
00:19:34,760 --> 00:19:36,901
Thank you.

259
00:19:36,901 --> 00:19:39,481
It's really delicious.

260
00:19:39,481 --> 00:19:42,091
Oh, that's right, Yeo Reum.

261
00:19:42,091 --> 00:19:44,371
I brought this for you.

262
00:19:44,371 --> 00:19:45,990
[Myeong Joo]

263
00:19:46,921 --> 00:19:48,111
What is this?

264
00:19:48,111 --> 00:19:51,481
It's the "Youth Angok." This came out today.

265
00:19:51,481 --> 00:19:53,471
Amazing!

266
00:19:58,700 --> 00:20:01,911
Wait, no way. Did you read it yet?

267
00:20:01,911 --> 00:20:03,821
No, I haven't read it yet.

268
00:20:03,821 --> 00:20:05,410
That's a relief.

269
00:20:05,410 --> 00:20:08,581
Please don't read it. I'm really not good at writing.

270
00:20:08,581 --> 00:20:10,241
That's not true.

271
00:20:10,241 --> 00:20:12,561
Wait, you said you didn't read it!

272
00:20:12,561 --> 00:20:14,471
I saw only the pictures, not the writing.

273
00:20:14,471 --> 00:20:18,481
I packed one for myself so I can read it right away when I get home tonight.

274
00:20:18,481 --> 00:20:21,020
No, please! Please don't read it.

275
00:20:21,020 --> 00:20:24,471
You'll be disappointed.

276
00:20:24,471 --> 00:20:26,271
What's going on?

277
00:20:26,271 --> 00:20:28,281
This b*stard!

278
00:20:28,281 --> 00:20:31,671
How dare you trip me?

279
00:20:31,671 --> 00:20:33,251
Ahjussi!

280
00:20:33,251 --> 00:20:35,561
Why is he making a loud fuss?

281
00:20:36,170 --> 00:20:39,031
- Are you okay, Sir?
- What a rude drunk.

282
00:20:39,031 --> 00:20:42,140
Don't touch me! Seriously. Hey, you!

283
00:20:42,140 --> 00:20:43,070
Don't look.

284
00:20:43,070 --> 00:20:47,751
I was okay only because I'm a former Marine who knew how to fall safely.

285
00:20:47,751 --> 00:20:50,610
If it were others, they would break their skulls.

286
00:20:50,610 --> 00:20:52,670
Be careful!

287
00:20:54,170 --> 00:20:55,731
Let go of me!

288
00:21:07,090 --> 00:21:09,351
Did something happen to you?

289
00:21:10,730 --> 00:21:14,071
I'll kill you if you tell anyone else.

290
00:21:14,071 --> 00:21:18,181
Nobody would believe you cried, even if I told them.

291
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:24,931
Thank you.

292
00:21:26,630 --> 00:21:28,431
What?

293
00:21:28,431 --> 00:21:31,321
You're the only one I have, really.

294
00:21:35,550 --> 00:21:37,201
I'll get going.

295
00:21:38,250 --> 00:21:41,621
Jo Ji Young, you can tell me any concerns.

296
00:21:41,621 --> 00:21:43,741
Your existence concerns me.

297
00:21:43,741 --> 00:21:49,641
I guess you feel better now since you speak coldly like usual.

298
00:21:51,220 --> 00:21:53,191
Bye.

299
00:21:53,191 --> 00:21:55,531
Drive safely.

300
00:21:56,790 --> 00:21:58,431
I'll get going.

301
00:21:59,790 --> 00:22:04,140
[Angok Public Library]

302
00:22:07,180 --> 00:22:09,181
Did she say I'm the only one she has?

303
00:22:11,910 --> 00:22:14,041
Am I the only one you have?

304
00:22:19,110 --> 00:22:20,511
- Did you enjoy the food?
- Yes.

305
00:22:20,511 --> 00:22:22,771
- How much is it?
- No, I've got this.

306
00:22:22,771 --> 00:22:24,421
No, please don't.

307
00:22:24,421 --> 00:22:26,940
It's already paid.

308
00:22:26,940 --> 00:22:29,451
It was paid by that man who tumbled outside.

309
00:22:29,451 --> 00:22:31,351
Really?

310
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:44,241
The beer was delicious, and we ate fried chicken for free.

311
00:22:44,241 --> 00:22:46,301
It's great.

312
00:22:48,670 --> 00:22:53,270
But I'm just wondering, do you ever get angry at all?

313
00:22:53,270 --> 00:22:56,911
I don't think I've ever seen you get upset.

314
00:22:59,940 --> 00:23:02,661
You could have been angry at that incident.

315
00:23:02,661 --> 00:23:06,751
Are you not angry, or are you holding it in?

316
00:23:07,920 --> 00:23:10,691
"I guess things like that happen."

317
00:23:11,810 --> 00:23:14,531
I think of it like that.

318
00:23:16,580 --> 00:23:19,151
I have to think that way in my life.

319
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:27,931
You're on another level than mine.

320
00:23:27,931 --> 00:23:31,731
It's not easy for me to think that way.

321
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:38,261
It takes a while for us to get home, right?

322
00:23:39,090 --> 00:23:42,591
Shall we play "hundred questions and answers"?

323
00:23:42,591 --> 00:23:44,541
"Hundred questions and answers"?

324
00:23:44,541 --> 00:23:48,511
Well, it seems I'll only ask the questions.

325
00:23:48,511 --> 00:23:50,241
Sounds good.

326
00:23:52,420 --> 00:23:55,621
What's your favorite fruit?

327
00:23:55,621 --> 00:23:57,911
My favorite fruit is an apple.

328
00:23:57,911 --> 00:24:00,641
You answered faster than expected!

329
00:24:02,040 --> 00:24:05,351
My favorite is strawberry.

330
00:24:05,351 --> 00:24:07,941
Oh, "strawberry."

331
00:24:07,941 --> 00:24:09,561
Then the next question...

332
00:24:09,561 --> 00:24:15,341
Then my next question, who is your favorite writer?

333
00:24:15,341 --> 00:24:19,181
Well... This is a hard one.

334
00:24:20,120 --> 00:24:22,251
Pick who comes to mind.

335
00:24:22,251 --> 00:24:25,651
I like Kim Ae-ran (wrote "My Brilliant Life").

336
00:24:26,590 --> 00:24:28,091
What about you, Dae Beom?

337
00:24:28,091 --> 00:24:31,000
My favorite is Carl Sagan (American astronomer).

338
00:24:31,000 --> 00:24:34,140
I enjoyed "Murmurs of Earth" so much.

339
00:24:34,141 --> 00:24:37,351
That suits you very well.

340
00:24:37,351 --> 00:24:40,201
Okay, last question!

341
00:24:40,201 --> 00:24:42,841
What's your favorite season?

342
00:24:42,841 --> 00:24:45,280
I like summer ("Yeo Reum").

343
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:48,711
I meant the summer season.

344
00:24:49,750 --> 00:24:54,641
I know. My favorite season is also summer.

345
00:24:58,780 --> 00:25:01,901
Can I ask one more? It's the final question, really.

346
00:25:01,901 --> 00:25:03,421
Of course.

347
00:25:04,830 --> 00:25:11,541
Why didn't you speak to me when we first met?

348
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:16,621
Well, actually,

349
00:25:16,621 --> 00:25:21,101
I find it difficult to talk to strangers.

350
00:25:21,101 --> 00:25:22,761
That's why.

351
00:25:25,220 --> 00:25:29,011
Then I guess you feel comfortable with me now.

352
00:25:29,011 --> 00:25:31,821
You spoke a lot with me today.

353
00:25:31,821 --> 00:25:35,521
Maybe that's why I feel like my throat is sore. Ahem.

354
00:25:37,010 --> 00:25:39,651
We didn't talk that much.

355
00:25:47,091 --> 00:25:50,831
[I know you're the one who killed Seon Ah. I saw it.]

356
00:25:53,350 --> 00:25:55,311
What's that?
[I know you're the one who killed Seon Ah. I saw it.]

357
00:26:03,180 --> 00:26:04,661
Are you okay?

358
00:26:04,661 --> 00:26:06,521
Yeo Reum, I'm sorry.

359
00:26:06,521 --> 00:26:08,981
Dae Beom.

360
00:26:08,981 --> 00:26:11,181
Dae Beom!

361
00:26:37,351 --> 00:26:39,141
[I know you're the one who killed Seon Ah.]

362
00:26:41,041 --> 00:26:42,831
[I saw it.]

363
00:27:38,260 --> 00:27:40,701
You better tell me the truth!

364
00:27:40,701 --> 00:27:42,041
I don't know.

365
00:27:42,041 --> 00:27:45,971
How dare you keep lying? You shouldn't lie here!

366
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:53,221
Dae Beom, you spoke well; why do you not talk suddenly?

367
00:27:53,221 --> 00:27:56,671
You said, "On my way home, I saw my father run away."

368
00:27:57,610 --> 00:27:59,180
Is that wrong?

369
00:27:59,851 --> 00:28:02,811
Dae Beom, look at me.

370
00:28:02,811 --> 00:28:05,571
I told you to look at me!

371
00:28:09,860 --> 00:28:14,861
Honestly, you are happy Seon Ah died, aren't you?

372
00:28:15,600 --> 00:28:17,781
You didn't like your sister.

373
00:28:18,810 --> 00:28:20,351
Right?

374
00:28:23,240 --> 00:28:25,020
It seems like you're right.

375
00:28:25,020 --> 00:28:27,740
He's happy his sister died.

376
00:28:31,030 --> 00:28:33,931
No. That's not true.

377
00:28:33,931 --> 00:28:36,491
That's not true!

378
00:28:39,110 --> 00:28:41,211
It's not true.

379
00:28:59,501 --> 00:29:01,301
[I know you're the one who killed Seon Ah.]

380
00:29:08,140 --> 00:29:10,540
[Pesticides]

381
00:29:20,481 --> 00:29:22,451
Dae Beom.

382
00:29:27,081 --> 00:29:29,291
Ahn Dae Beom!

383
00:29:37,781 --> 00:29:39,541
Oh, you're here.

384
00:29:39,541 --> 00:29:41,811
Who pulled up the shutter?

385
00:29:41,811 --> 00:29:44,891
- Did you pull it up, Mr. Kwak?
- No, I didn't.

386
00:29:44,891 --> 00:29:47,401
Hey, go ahead and pull it down.

387
00:29:50,481 --> 00:29:52,351
What kind of crazy b*stard did this?

388
00:29:52,351 --> 00:29:54,601
They did this sh*t again!

389
00:29:54,601 --> 00:29:57,571
"I know you're the one who killed Seon Ah."

390
00:29:59,301 --> 00:30:02,301
"I saw it"?

391
00:30:02,301 --> 00:30:05,151
The one who killed Seon Ah was her father!

392
00:30:05,151 --> 00:30:08,901
Father, I think we need to report this to the police, or it may become a bigger problem.

393
00:30:08,901 --> 00:30:11,621
Then word will spread to the county; that's not good.

394
00:30:11,621 --> 00:30:14,331
How is that the issue right now?

395
00:30:14,331 --> 00:30:19,411
Seriously! What kind of karma do I have with Seon Ah's household?

396
00:30:19,411 --> 00:30:22,651
Father! Watch your words!

397
00:30:23,311 --> 00:30:27,611
Dae Beom, that punk! I overlooked it because I felt bad for him, but...

398
00:30:27,611 --> 00:30:29,971
He's a victim.

399
00:30:29,971 --> 00:30:31,651
What?

400
00:30:31,651 --> 00:30:34,511
Dae Beom is the biggest victim here.

401
00:30:34,511 --> 00:30:37,151
Yes, good that you brought it up.

402
00:30:37,151 --> 00:30:39,331
Did I kill his sister and his mother?

403
00:30:39,331 --> 00:30:43,641
Because they died, this building turned into a useless thing!

404
00:30:43,641 --> 00:30:45,831
The victim of that is me! Me!

405
00:30:45,831 --> 00:30:49,081
Ahjussi, please calm down.

406
00:30:49,081 --> 00:30:53,701
Let me put a surveillance camera right here as the first step.

407
00:30:53,701 --> 00:30:56,741
Yes, a surveillance camera!

408
00:30:56,741 --> 00:30:59,291
We should have put one up a while ago.

409
00:30:59,291 --> 00:31:03,261
Mu Cheol, thank you. You're the only one I can rely on.

410
00:31:05,281 --> 00:31:07,031
Yeo Reum.

411
00:31:10,371 --> 00:31:15,041
If you see anyone suspicious, please contact me right away.

412
00:31:16,261 --> 00:31:17,561
I will.

413
00:31:17,561 --> 00:31:20,471
Hello, Professor. This is Reporter Park Cheol Hyun from "Tomorrow's News."

414
00:31:20,471 --> 00:31:23,921
- I won't take any interviews. Bye.
- Wait! One second, Sir.

415
00:31:23,921 --> 00:31:26,791
Someone reported on your recent paper in the science community.

416
00:31:26,791 --> 00:31:29,171
I don't have any time. Bye.

417
00:31:29,171 --> 00:31:31,881
Professor? Professor?

418
00:31:31,881 --> 00:31:36,231
Professor, I think you need to see this.

419
00:31:36,231 --> 00:31:39,001
This is up on the anonymous community.

420
00:31:39,001 --> 00:31:41,011
What is this?

421
00:31:41,011 --> 00:31:45,521
It says you paid to take someone else's idea so people are wild right now.

422
00:31:45,521 --> 00:31:48,011
"Took someone else's idea"?

423
00:31:48,011 --> 00:31:51,291
They don't know what's going on.

424
00:31:51,291 --> 00:31:55,961
This might become a bigger issue if Sunbae Dae Beom doesn't show up in person.

425
00:31:55,961 --> 00:31:59,291
The university president will meet Ethics Committee.

426
00:31:59,291 --> 00:32:02,781
"Ethics Committee"? Then what happens next?

427
00:32:02,781 --> 00:32:06,751
In the worst-case scenario, both of them can be banned from academia,

428
00:32:06,751 --> 00:32:10,881
since selling an idea is a huge issue in this field.

429
00:32:10,881 --> 00:32:13,711
So Sunbae Dae Beom may get dragged into it and be harmed.

430
00:32:13,711 --> 00:32:15,561
Dae Beom as well?

431
00:32:15,561 --> 00:32:16,991
Yes.

432
00:32:16,991 --> 00:32:22,321
So he must show up to the ethics committee and tell the truth.

433
00:32:22,321 --> 00:32:24,151
Please ask him to come.

434
00:32:27,551 --> 00:32:33,311
Okay. I'll call you later after talking to Dae Beom.

435
00:32:34,211 --> 00:32:36,191
Hello.

436
00:32:36,991 --> 00:32:39,721
Where's Dae Beom?

437
00:32:39,721 --> 00:32:41,731
"Dae Beom."

438
00:32:42,301 --> 00:32:44,821
He hasn't come to work yet.

439
00:32:47,631 --> 00:32:50,001
By any chance...

440
00:32:50,001 --> 00:32:52,951
Did something happen between you two last night?

441
00:32:55,221 --> 00:32:57,031
The thing is...

442
00:32:58,581 --> 00:33:01,871
Why are you obsessing over things like this?

443
00:33:01,871 --> 00:33:04,101
It's just a short trip, not a sixtieth birthday.

444
00:33:04,101 --> 00:33:06,771
I'm sorry. I went overboard shopping.

445
00:33:06,771 --> 00:33:10,291
It seems a lot, but we'll eat it all. Right?

446
00:33:13,051 --> 00:33:15,301
Hey, where are you going?

447
00:33:15,301 --> 00:33:17,131
What? Won't you come in?

448
00:33:17,131 --> 00:33:18,451
This is my place.

449
00:33:18,451 --> 00:33:21,111
- This house?
- Yes.

450
00:33:21,911 --> 00:33:23,681
Come in.

451
00:33:27,321 --> 00:33:30,311
You can put the groceries over here.

452
00:33:32,861 --> 00:33:35,951
Is this really your house?

453
00:33:35,951 --> 00:33:38,151
No, it's my aunt's place.

454
00:33:38,151 --> 00:33:40,011
Our homeroom teacher?

455
00:33:40,011 --> 00:33:42,231
Did you know that?

456
00:33:42,231 --> 00:33:44,531
I bet all in school know besides you and her.

457
00:33:44,531 --> 00:33:47,511
You two always talk at the back in teacher's room.

458
00:33:47,511 --> 00:33:49,781
You all knew it.

459
00:33:50,591 --> 00:33:52,850
But the homeroom teacher...

460
00:33:52,850 --> 00:33:56,711
So your aunt was this rich?

461
00:33:56,711 --> 00:33:59,591
It's complicated to say it. But come over here.

462
00:33:59,591 --> 00:34:03,731
My dad bought this house for her to keep an eye on me.

463
00:34:03,731 --> 00:34:05,551
Have a seat here.

464
00:34:07,521 --> 00:34:10,871
I guess it must be uncomfortable for you to live with your aunt.

465
00:34:10,871 --> 00:34:13,711
- She doesn't live here.
- What?

466
00:34:13,711 --> 00:34:16,391
Do you use this gigantic house all by yourself?

467
00:34:16,391 --> 00:34:19,101
Actually, I use only this space on the first floor.

468
00:34:19,101 --> 00:34:20,401
Why?

469
00:34:20,401 --> 00:34:22,571
I don't know. Sit there and have a rest.

470
00:34:22,571 --> 00:34:24,371
It's okay. Let's do it together.

471
00:34:24,371 --> 00:34:26,821
I'd appreciate your help.

472
00:34:29,001 --> 00:34:31,621
What's going on?

473
00:34:31,621 --> 00:34:34,311
Why is this big fridge so empty?

474
00:34:34,311 --> 00:34:36,271
Don't you like cooking?

475
00:34:36,271 --> 00:34:38,751
Cooking's meaning is not eating, but doing it for someone else.

476
00:34:38,751 --> 00:34:41,361
On my own, I just eat whatever.

477
00:34:44,141 --> 00:34:47,901
Bom, can you peel some pears for me?

478
00:34:50,201 --> 00:34:52,431
I think somebody came home.

479
00:34:54,091 --> 00:34:56,311
It's a beautiful house.

480
00:34:57,161 --> 00:34:58,751
Hi.

481
00:34:58,751 --> 00:35:00,901
Aunt, why come here out of the blue?

482
00:35:00,901 --> 00:35:04,201
I told you a new English teacher is coming today.

483
00:35:04,961 --> 00:35:08,811
But what's all this? And why is she here?

484
00:35:08,811 --> 00:35:10,981
Aunt, the thing is...

485
00:35:10,981 --> 00:35:13,241
Heo Jae Hoon, let's talk for a second.

486
00:35:13,241 --> 00:35:16,191
Thomas, wait a minute. I'm sorry.

487
00:35:16,191 --> 00:35:19,641
- No problem. Take your time.
- Thank you.

488
00:35:19,641 --> 00:35:22,041
Bom, I'm sorry. Excuse me a second.

489
00:35:26,381 --> 00:35:30,981
Heo Jae Hoon! Why are you doing this, seriously?

490
00:35:30,981 --> 00:35:33,021
- Hi.
- How many times must I tell you?

491
00:35:33,021 --> 00:35:35,931
You wouldn't act this way if you consider your parents!

492
00:35:35,931 --> 00:35:38,461
You can't act this way!

493
00:36:27,131 --> 00:36:30,201
Stand up. Let's go to the hospital.

494
00:36:32,211 --> 00:36:34,411
I said stand up.

495
00:36:37,741 --> 00:36:42,041
I... I'm fine.

496
00:36:43,341 --> 00:36:45,091
Okay then.

497
00:36:45,881 --> 00:36:48,961
Live or die, do whatever you want by yourself.

498
00:36:58,351 --> 00:37:01,601
I've warned you! I won't say this twice.

499
00:37:02,691 --> 00:37:04,271
Jae Hoon, I'll get going.

500
00:37:04,271 --> 00:37:07,441
Hey! Listen well.

501
00:37:07,441 --> 00:37:12,091
I don't know your scheme, but if you call him again, I won't leave you alone.

502
00:37:13,871 --> 00:37:16,051
Heo Jae Hoon.

503
00:37:16,051 --> 00:37:17,771
Do you hate hanging out with me?

504
00:37:17,771 --> 00:37:19,461
Wait, what?

505
00:37:20,431 --> 00:37:22,461
No, I love it.

506
00:37:22,461 --> 00:37:24,611
I like it the most.

507
00:37:24,611 --> 00:37:27,661
See? He chases after me.

508
00:37:27,661 --> 00:37:30,571
Look how this girl speaks! Do you want to get expelled from school?

509
00:37:30,571 --> 00:37:32,091
Bom, let's go together.

510
00:37:32,091 --> 00:37:34,011
Heo Jae Hoon! Where are you going?

511
00:37:34,011 --> 00:37:35,941
I'll tell your dad everything.

512
00:37:35,941 --> 00:37:38,211
Do as you wish.

513
00:37:38,211 --> 00:37:43,431
Hey, Thomas. She is a very bad aunt.

514
00:37:43,431 --> 00:37:45,361
I heard everything as well.

515
00:37:45,361 --> 00:37:46,801
Thomas!

516
00:37:46,801 --> 00:37:48,431
What?

517
00:38:00,191 --> 00:38:01,741
- Nurse Kim.
- Yes?

518
00:38:01,741 --> 00:38:04,531
- Give him a shot.
- Okay.

519
00:38:04,531 --> 00:38:07,221
- Get the shot before you go.
- Okay.

520
00:38:07,221 --> 00:38:09,371
Please come this way.

521
00:38:16,101 --> 00:38:17,661
How is he?

522
00:38:17,661 --> 00:38:22,661
Trauma isn't easily forgotten, even if they say they forgot everything;

523
00:38:22,661 --> 00:38:25,571
your body is smarter than you think.

524
00:38:26,151 --> 00:38:28,021
You know he needs an emotional rest, right?

525
00:38:28,021 --> 00:38:29,651
Yes.

526
00:38:30,291 --> 00:38:33,221
Just let him do what he wants to do.

527
00:38:33,221 --> 00:38:35,171
We have to wait and see.

528
00:38:35,171 --> 00:38:36,761
Lie down comfortably here.

529
00:38:36,761 --> 00:38:40,101
Is he in a bad state?

530
00:38:40,101 --> 00:38:43,771
Yes, he's not in a great state.

531
00:38:43,771 --> 00:38:48,671
I'll increase his medication; make sure he takes it regularly.

532
00:38:48,671 --> 00:38:50,041
Yes, I will.

533
00:38:50,041 --> 00:38:52,401
Good. But that is it.

534
00:38:52,401 --> 00:38:54,601
When will you two invite me to your wedding?

535
00:38:54,601 --> 00:38:56,071
Next patient, please come to the office.

536
00:38:56,071 --> 00:38:59,361
I told you! We are not like that.

537
00:38:59,361 --> 00:39:01,871
It's because he's not good at expressing his feelings!

538
00:39:01,871 --> 00:39:03,431
It's not like that.

539
00:39:04,511 --> 00:39:06,461
By the way,

540
00:39:06,461 --> 00:39:09,281
who wrote that graffiti?

541
00:39:21,541 --> 00:39:23,601
Seon Ah, die.

542
00:39:23,601 --> 00:39:26,291
Kill Seon Ah. Seon Ah, die.

543
00:39:26,291 --> 00:39:28,631
Kill Seon Ah. Seon Ah, die.

544
00:39:28,631 --> 00:39:30,691
Kill Seon Ah. Seon Ah, die!

545
00:39:30,691 --> 00:39:33,151
Kill Seon Ah. Seon Ah, die!

546
00:39:33,151 --> 00:39:34,801
Kill Seon Ah! Kill Seon Ah!

547
00:39:34,801 --> 00:39:37,551
She's not Seon Ah, Geun Ho!

548
00:39:37,551 --> 00:39:39,221
- Okay? Please!
- No, kill Seon Ah.

549
00:39:39,221 --> 00:39:41,961
Please get yourself together, can you?

550
00:39:41,961 --> 00:39:44,561
Geun Ho, look at me. Look at Mom's face.

551
00:39:44,561 --> 00:39:46,771
If you do that again, I'll call the police.

552
00:39:46,771 --> 00:39:49,671
The policeman is scary! The policeman is scary!

553
00:39:49,671 --> 00:39:51,661
Geun Ho!

554
00:39:51,661 --> 00:39:53,491
The policeman is scary!

555
00:39:53,491 --> 00:39:57,981
- Seon Ah is in danger. Seon Ah is in danger...
- It's okay, Geun Ho. Please calm down.

556
00:40:01,831 --> 00:40:03,591
Noona.

557
00:40:05,641 --> 00:40:07,811
You were...

558
00:40:10,341 --> 00:40:13,411
friends with my sister.

559
00:40:16,191 --> 00:40:18,281
Did you like her?

560
00:40:19,671 --> 00:40:21,801
We weren't friends.

561
00:40:21,801 --> 00:40:24,701
She was the sky, and I was the ground.

562
00:40:29,631 --> 00:40:32,061
I didn't like her.

563
00:40:38,141 --> 00:40:41,301
Because of my sister,

564
00:40:44,961 --> 00:40:47,791
I was scolded by my father every day.

565
00:41:21,691 --> 00:41:25,081
What brings you all the way here?

566
00:41:30,121 --> 00:41:32,341
This is how you live here.

567
00:41:32,341 --> 00:41:34,281
Let me sit down.

568
00:41:37,221 --> 00:41:39,371
How is...

569
00:41:39,371 --> 00:41:42,031
How is Dae Beom?

570
00:41:42,031 --> 00:41:47,451
He got a sedative at the hospital. I'm back from laying him down at his place.

571
00:41:47,451 --> 00:41:49,391
Did he go to a hospital?

572
00:41:54,741 --> 00:41:56,611
Yeo Reum.

573
00:41:57,351 --> 00:42:01,061
You said you heard what happened here before, right?

574
00:42:01,901 --> 00:42:05,401
Yes. I heard it from Bom.

575
00:42:06,501 --> 00:42:12,401
Did you hear who found the body first when Dae Beom's sister died?

576
00:42:14,701 --> 00:42:16,661
It was Dae Beom.

577
00:42:17,551 --> 00:42:22,091
Also, the one who found Dae Beom's mother after she committed suicide

578
00:42:22,091 --> 00:42:23,911
was Dae Beom.

579
00:42:24,791 --> 00:42:30,481
He's already having a hard time just because you are living in this building.

580
00:42:30,481 --> 00:42:33,771
It'll keep reminding him of the past.

581
00:42:33,771 --> 00:42:38,931
He thinks he killed all his family members.

582
00:42:40,711 --> 00:42:42,861
What about Bom's hospital bill?

583
00:42:42,861 --> 00:42:45,201
Do you know who paid for it?

584
00:42:45,201 --> 00:42:47,781
Her hospital bill? Did he?

585
00:42:47,781 --> 00:42:52,311
Since you were stressed out about Bom's hospital bill,

586
00:42:52,311 --> 00:42:57,771
Dae Beom called his former professor and sold the paper he wrote

587
00:42:57,771 --> 00:42:59,821
so he could pay Bom's hospital bill.

588
00:43:02,141 --> 00:43:06,911
But due to that, the professor who helped Dae Beom is now in trouble.

589
00:43:06,911 --> 00:43:11,081
And if Dae Beom doesn't go to Seoul right now,

590
00:43:11,081 --> 00:43:14,001
too many things will be messed up.

591
00:43:14,001 --> 00:43:16,021
Why did this happen?

592
00:43:17,121 --> 00:43:19,271
Yeo Reum.

593
00:43:19,271 --> 00:43:21,301
Do you like Dae Beom?

594
00:43:22,051 --> 00:43:23,061
Pardon?

595
00:43:23,061 --> 00:43:25,451
But I don't care about that anymore.

596
00:43:25,451 --> 00:43:29,031
I don't care if you have feelings for him or not.

597
00:43:29,031 --> 00:43:34,961
I just really hate that Dae Beom's life keeps getting worse because of you.

598
00:43:35,701 --> 00:43:39,801
Do you know how hard it is for Dae Beom to live?

599
00:43:39,801 --> 00:43:43,361
He just runs every day without sleeping.

600
00:43:43,361 --> 00:43:45,701
He's always alone.

601
00:43:45,701 --> 00:43:47,481
That's how he survived.

602
00:43:47,481 --> 00:43:51,421
He tried his best to endure with all his strength.

603
00:43:51,421 --> 00:43:54,201
But that all collapsed today.

604
00:43:54,941 --> 00:43:57,601
If he goes into his room like now,

605
00:43:58,431 --> 00:44:04,091
I have no idea when he'll be able to come out again.

606
00:44:08,781 --> 00:44:10,171
I'm sorry.

607
00:44:10,171 --> 00:44:14,001
No, anyone can say sorry.

608
00:44:14,001 --> 00:44:16,301
Yeo Reum.

609
00:44:16,301 --> 00:44:18,571
Can you take responsibility?

610
00:44:19,961 --> 00:44:24,411
Can you take responsibility for Dae Beom's life?

611
00:44:25,691 --> 00:44:27,651
I can do it.

612
00:44:27,651 --> 00:44:31,181
I did it until now; I'll do it in the future as well.

613
00:44:32,861 --> 00:44:34,951
Yeo Reum, for you,

614
00:44:35,611 --> 00:44:38,291
it might be just a summer fling in a beach town,

615
00:44:38,291 --> 00:44:40,191
but my relationship with Dae Beom is different.

616
00:44:40,191 --> 00:44:42,881
It's not like that for me.

617
00:44:44,521 --> 00:44:47,211
If not then please help me.

618
00:44:48,801 --> 00:44:54,521
If you won't leave this place, please help Dae Beom to go.

619
00:44:55,851 --> 00:44:57,851
I beg of you.

620
00:45:01,011 --> 00:45:02,841
Please help him once.

621
00:45:33,161 --> 00:45:35,221
Will you be okay?

622
00:45:36,571 --> 00:45:40,231
I'll beg my aunt's forgiveness when I get home.

623
00:45:40,231 --> 00:45:42,121
That sounds like you.

624
00:45:43,441 --> 00:45:46,111
Thank you, Bom.

625
00:45:47,371 --> 00:45:48,991
For what?

626
00:45:50,101 --> 00:45:52,101
Just everything.

627
00:45:53,961 --> 00:45:58,341
I'm envious you can act like that.

628
00:45:58,341 --> 00:46:00,601
Did you say you envy me?

629
00:46:00,601 --> 00:46:03,111
- I envy you.
- Of me?

630
00:46:03,111 --> 00:46:04,951
Yes.

631
00:46:04,951 --> 00:46:07,071
You are rich.

632
00:46:11,221 --> 00:46:16,041
I think you are richer than I am.

633
00:46:17,291 --> 00:46:21,071
You have Ha Neul and your grandmother.

634
00:46:31,061 --> 00:46:34,491
By the way, what if our homeroom teacher really expels me?

635
00:46:34,491 --> 00:46:37,751
Please talk well of me to her when you get home.

636
00:46:38,821 --> 00:46:41,641
If she says so, I'll say I'll quit school, too.

